<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Congressional Committee Seizes Cotton Chamber Documents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1603133294 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 15 Mar 94 p 21 </F>
<F P=103> PY1603133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Congressional Investigating Committee on 
Illegal Activities (CBII), in an unexpected action, yesterday 
raided the Paraguayan Cotton Chamber (Cadelpa) and seized a 
great quantity of documents (acts of the last few years, and 15 
recorded hours of sessions) that bring to light the 
oligopolistic procedures used by that organization to impose a 
national cotton price on the country's peasants, as well as 
control the administration of all stages of the production and 
marketing of "white gold." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

