<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economy Minister Regrets U.S. Withdrawal From Support Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1603132794 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1603132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] After attending a meeting with the congressional 
Agriculture Committee, Economy Minister Jorge Camet said that 
the bonus for schoolchildren will be paid to workers at the 
beginning of April, and will amount to something between 120 and 
150 soles. [passage omitted] 
  The minister added that the funds raised from the 
privatization process will be used on social programs. [passage 
omitted] 
  The economy minister also reported that the government is 
preparing the last details of the letter of intent it will sign 
with the IMF. He stated categorically that Peru will not insist 
that the United States comply with its offer to participate in 
the support group. 
  [Begin Camet recording] I regret to say that the United 
States is the only country that has not complied with its 
promise to join the support group. All the other countries that 
had promised to do so complied with their promises, (?except) 
for the U.S. Government. It is their decision, and we respect 
it. Any money we can get is welcome, but if someone promises to 
give money and now does not want to give it... [end recording] 

</TEXT>

