<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Workers Donate Record Amount to Finance Militia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1103145494 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1324 GMT 9 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA1103145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 9 Mar (PL) -- More than 27 million pesos, 
which is equivalent to $27 million at the official exchange 
rate, was donated during 1993 by workers to finance Territorial 
Militia Troops (MTT), Cuba's largest defense corps. 
  The Cuban Workers Federation (CTC), which is comprised of 
all 
the country's unions, said today that this was a record 
collection among Cuban workers for this purpose. 
  The MTT, formed by volunteers from all Cuban neighborhoods, 
are comprised of several million people and their main task is 
to support the regular troops in repelling and defeating any 
enemy aggression. 
  Cuba's concept of defense is basically based in popular 
participation in fighting foreign invaders, and it is called the 
war of all the people. 
  The CTC said, in a report on the donations to finance these 
militias, that more than 4 million pesos collected was payment 
for voluntary work. 

</TEXT>

