<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank President: Difficult Year Ahead </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1503135994 </F>
<F P=103> PA1503135994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] San Pedro Sula TIEMPO in Spanish on 10 
March, page 5, reports that on 9 March after meeting with the 
Honduran Exporters Association, Hugo Noe Pino, president of the 
Central Bank of Honduras, said the reactivation of public 
investment will decrease this year. Noe Pino said this will be a 
difficult year for Hondurans because of the high fiscal deficit 
left by the previous government. Noe Pino said it will also be 
difficult because price freezes will be lifted and fluctuations 
are expected in the exchange rate. Noe Pino added, however, that 
the family basket tax will not increase. An tax increase on 
luxury items is being analyzed, he noted. 

</TEXT>

