  [Text] Opposition to the president-in-exile is in motion. 
Citing the political vacuum that has existed since the 
resignation of Prime Minister Robert Malval in mid-December 
1993, the national coalition [not further identified] has 
charged the Army with responsiblity for assuming power, or of 
supporting the formation of an ad hoc government. Let us listen 
to the coalition's spokesman, Mr. Brutus: 
