entire nation, the National Coalition, concerned with the 
extreme peril that has been brought upon the Haitian nation, 
solemnly charges the Haitian Armed Forces to put an end to the 
drifting of the Haitian ship, either by temporarily assuming the 
country's leadership, or by facilitating the implementation of 
an ad hoc government in charge of conducting the state of Haiti 
through the difficult times it is facing. 
  Port-au-Prince, 15 March 1994. Carl Denis, secretary 
general; 
Patrick Brutus, spokesman. [end recording] 

