<H3> <TI>   Nicaragua Appoints Permanent Observer to Parlacen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1903123194 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2341 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1903123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 17 March (ACAN-EFE) -- The 
Nicaraguan Government today appointed its ambassador to 
Guatemala, Mauricio Diaz Davila, as permanent observer to the 
Central American Parliament (Parlacen). 
  Salvadoran citizen Jose Francisco Guerrero, president of the 
Parlacen, explained that the diplomat's appointment is temporary 
until Nicaragua, which has already ratified the charter for this 
regional forum, elects its 20 representatives. 
  He added that Nicaraguan Foreign Minister Ernesto Leal 
notified him in writing of Diaz' appointment as permanent 
observer, given "the importance of Parlacen meetings." 
  The Parlacen was created three years ago as a regional forum 
to discuss the area's political, economic, and social issues. 
So far only Guatemala, El Salvador, and Honduras have appointed 
representatives, while Costa Rica and Panama have yet to ratify 
the charter. 

</TEXT>

