<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   3-80 Northern Front, Government Reach Compromise </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1803170094 Managua Radio Corporacion in Spanish 2300 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1803170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Corporacion </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Five O'Clock Sharp" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A serious impasse between the government and the 
rearmed groups of the 3-80 Northern Front was overcome yesterday. 
  The demobilized members of the 3-80 Northern Front, 
following 
orders from its Council of Commanders headed by Jose Angel 
Talavera Alaniz, alias El Chacal, had decided to suspend their 
disarmament because the government was unable to fulfill its 
promises made during the disarmament negotiations. It 
definitely created a serious concern among the political, 
economic, and social circles that see in the 3-80 Northern Front 
the most serious threat to the Nicaraguan peace process. 
  Salvador Talavera Alaniz, alias Esteban, brother of Jose 
Angel Talavera, El Chacal, who was the political leader of the 
armed group for a long time, said they were able to reach a 
compromise with the Government Ministry to fulfill the 
agreements reached in Quilali last week when the first meetings 
between the 3-80 Northern Front Council of Commanders and the 
Government Ministry began. 
  Now that the impasse has been overcome, the former armed 
groups will be able to purchase the lands they need. The former 
armed groups need more than 1,300 manzanas of lands to return to 
civilian life. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

