<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disarmament Process To Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1903151294 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1217 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1903151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 19 Mar (DPA) -- The 3-80 Northern Front, 
the largest group of armed rebels in Nicaragua since the 
disarmament of the Nicaraguan Resistance (contras), announced 
today after a series of agreements were reached with President 
Violeta Chamorro's government it will continue the disarmament 
process. 
  Jose Angel Talavera (El Chacal), the rebels' leader, said in 
Managua next week his men, estimated at more than 200, will 
continue to turn in their weapons in the Quilali region, 
approximately 320 km north of Managua. 
  The armed group suspended the disarmament process last week, 
fearing the government would not meet its commitments. Talavera 
said he hopes this time the government will meet its commitment 
with the demobilized, adding on previous occasions it had not. 
  The government offered a series of social benefits for the 
contras' disarmament; nevertheless, there are constant protests 
against the government's lack of fulfillment. 

</TEXT>

