<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Robaina Continues Asia Trip </TI></H3>
<H4>   Concludes Visit to India </H4>
<F P=102> FL1903182894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1903182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Indian Prime Minister P.V. Narasimha Rao met with 
Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina. During that meeting in 
New Delhi, Robaina gave Rao a message from Commander in Chief 
Fidel Castro, president of the Councils of State and of 
Ministers. Rao said that his country is interested in 
strengthening its bilateral relations with Cuba. After his 
meeting with the head of the Indian Government, Robaina stated 
that Cuba opposes foreign intervention in India's domestic 
affairs and highlighted India's important role in the Nonaligned 
Movement. Robaina concluded his official visit to India and 
departed for Malaysia as part of his tour through Asia, which 
will conclude in Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

