<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Robaina Continues Asia Trip </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Malaysian Counterpart </H4>
<F P=102> FL2003214394 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 
20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2003214394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah bin Haji Ahmad 
Badawi acknowledged, in a meeting with Cuban Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina, that Cuba is clearly making progress and that 
under no pretext should anyone exert pressure on that country. 
  Robaina arrived in the Malaysian capital yesterday from 
India. In an exchange, his counterpart reiterated that it is the 
Cubans who alone must determine their fate -- an allusion to the 
U.S. policy against Cuba. The Malaysian foreign minister also 
expressed his satisfaction with the Cuban Foreign Ministry's new 
policy of rapprochement with the region, and stressed that he is 
willing to form a businessmen's delegation to visit Havana over 
the next few months to increase trade between the two nations. 
  Robaina agreed with the Malaysian foreign minister on the 
need to take practical steps toward progress in the world of 
communication. Robaina said: We are here to learn about and 
assess the experiences of countries that, like this one, have 
enjoyed sustained development. 

</TEXT>

