<H4>   Miami Poll on Ending Embargo Cited </H4>
<F P=102> FL1903184994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1903184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Several U.S. sectors have indicated that U.S. 
President Clinton maintains the U.S. blockade on Cuba because he 
considers it of strategic importance in obtaining the votes in 
the State of Florida for his reelection in 1996. Nevertheless, 
a recent survey indicates that 40 percent of Hispanic residents 
in Miami favor the lifting of the U.S. blockade. 

</TEXT>

