<H3> <TI>   Cuban Ballerina Waits For U.S. Visa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1803160394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1803160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Just four days before the Oscars ceremony in the 
United States, Cuban Ballerina Alicia Alonso, a special guest to 
the ceremony, still has not received a visa to enter U.S. 
territory. Alonso has just confirmed for PRENSA LATINA that 
permission to enter the United States has not been granted to 
her nor to dancers Rosario Suarez, or Liang Chen, who are also 
members of Cuba's national ballet company. 
  Just four days before the Oscar ceremony, our Alicia Alonso 
still has not received a visa to enter U.S. territory. 

</TEXT>

