<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plenum Held on Parliaments in the Workplace </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ross Leal on Analyzing Efficiency </H4>
<F P=102> FL1803205694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1803205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday in Bayamo, Politburo member Pedro Ross 
Leal, secretary general of the Cuban Workers Federation [CTC], 
said the workers parliaments have expressed their support for 
economic efficiency. In a meeting to evaluate the progress of 
this process in Granma Province, which Alfredo Enriquez Pina, 
first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba [PCC] in Granma 
Province, also attended, Ross Leal noted that the solution to 
our problems is not money but more production. He stated that as 
long as 79 percent of the country's enterprises are 
unprofitable, Cuba will not be able to improve or overcome the 
special period. He stressed that it was essential to reduce 
expenses and increase production. He pointed out that until 
production is raised we cannot think of an analysis of 
agriculture prices. He went on to say that 
agricultural-livestock workers first need to produce enough for 
themselves and for the rest of our people. 
  During this meeting to analyze the workers parliaments of 
Granma Province, it was mentioned that the Basic Cooperative 
Production Units [UBPC] have been created but the number of 
management personnel of the enterprises and delegations of the 
Ministry of the Sugar Industry and the Ministry of Agriculture 
have not been reduced. The importance of implementing a set of 
ideas previously submitted by workers was also stressed by 
participants. The solution to many of those problems can be 
found in the individual work center, municipality, or province. 
  [Begin Ross recording] On the 29th we will agree on what we 
will call the process that will follow this one, because we do 
not want the word parliament to lose its content. The name 
should express what is desired and it should be used when that 
is necessary. We are going to change the focus and the name of 
our process of assemblies of production or services. We are 
thinking that they should be assemblies to discuss economic 
efficiency in production or service centers. We must analyze 
this carefully to establish a proper name so that they are not 
used for something else, because production or services 
assemblies are good for everything except for the analysis of 
these problems. [end recording] 
  During the meeting, Pedro Ross Leal awarded a banner to 
Granma Province for being the largest contributor toward 
financing the Territorial Troops Militia [MTT] during 1993. In a 
coming contact, we will offer exclusive statements made for this 
program by comrade Ross Leal giving his personal views of the 
progress of the workers parliaments in Granma Province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-11276 </DOCNO>
