<H3> <TI>   MiG Aircraft Crashes; Two Pilots Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1803135794 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1803135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of the Revolutionary Armed Forces 
[Minfar] has reported that an unfortunate accident took place on 
the morning of 17 March, involving a two-seat MiG-23UB 
[alphanumeric designation as heard] aircraft carrying out a 
highly complex training flight over the territory of the Eastern 
Army. 
  Two first class pilots from Holguin Airbase died in this 
accident. They are: Major Sinecio Landa Lopez, married, and 
father of two children, and Major Jose Borrego Pajon, also 
married, who left a pregnant wife. 
  Both pilots are graduates from our aviation school in Pinar 
del Rio in 1985 and 1986. They were 36 years old, militants of 
the Cuban Communist Party, and both fulfilled internationalist 
missions in Angola. 
  The Minfar has conveyed condolences to all relatives of 
these 
two courageous pilots who died in the fulfillment of their tasks. 

</TEXT>

