<H3> <TI>   Western Army Labor Protection Campaign Under Way </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2003223194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2003223194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] How to guarantee the safety of machines and 
equipment, increase workers' competency, and achieve general 
combat readiness are the topics being discussed today by the 
Western Army's first inspection and labor protection campaign. 
For the past few months, the units of the Western Army's 
territory have been making great efforts to guarantee every 
worker the resources that will allow him to do his work with a 
maximum of security for his life. Also, existing technical 
difficulties in various types of equipment -- especially that 
used in engineering tasks -- have been solved by means of 
interesting innovations. Regrettable work accidents have thereby 
been avoided. Among those centers with best results is the 
Western Army's rearguard technical safety unit [unidad de 
aseguramiento tecnico de retaguardia], which has made over 1,800 
gloves for use in soldering or in agricultural activities. 
  Sixteen papers are being analyzed here today, selected from 
the 50 submitted at the grassroots level. A jury will choose the 
best six, which will then be presented at the Army's ninth 
science and technology forum. They will also (?be presented) in 
the campaign at the level of the [entire] Armed Forces, 
scheduled for 14 and 15 June, which happens to be the 20th 
anniversary of the [creation of the] FAR's [Revolutionary Armed 
Forces'] technical inspection and labor protection specialty. 

</TEXT>

