teaching hospital, said he performed six operations and held a 
practicum workshop during which aspects of orthopedics were 
assessed. Alvarez Cambras explained that two protocols of intent 
were signed: one, on exchange of information in metallurgy and 
the development of orthopedic instruments and parts; the other, 
with the Social Security Hospital where our doctors will go 
several times a year to train specialists. 

