<H3> <TI>   Cuba's Robaina To Visit in April To Discuss Debt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2003184794 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2144 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2003184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 19 Mar (NA) -- Cuban Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina will visit Argentina in April to negotiate with 
the administration of President Carlos Menem a debt contracted 
by Cuba during the seventies, during Juan Domingo Peron's 
presidency. 
  Argentine diplomats have always believed that the debt, 
contracted through the export of trucks and other vehicles to 
Cuba during Peron's last term, was "irrecoverable." 
  Cuba had offered to Argentina to pay the debt through 
tourist 
leasings in the island, as it lacks the cash to pay it. 
  Robaina's visit would take place at the completion of the 
negotiations undertaken by Cuban diplomats at the Argentine 
Foreign Ministry to renegotiate the debt. 

