<H3> <TI>   Peligre Power Station Shut Down for Repairs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1803180694 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1803180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Electricity of Haiti [EDH] has decided to cease 
completely the exploitation of the Peligre hydroelectric power 
station because the artificial lake has reached its minimum 
level of 153 meters. During the shutdown, repair and 
maintenance will be carried out at the power station on two of 
the three turbines in order to take the maximum advantage of the 
next rainy season expected during the month of May. 
  According to an EDH announcement, the work should last four 
weeks. EDH will guarantee 100 1.326369e-315xploitability of the production 
capacity of the hydroelectric power station, that is 54 MW, as 
soon as the level of the lake goes back up with the heavy rains 
of May. EDH hopes to reduce rationing soon and to maintain 
reasonable service throughout the grid in the capital. 
  We should also say that mud patches have allegedly reached 
the shores of the lake and have even allegedly reached the 
turbines, according to inhabitants in the area contacted by 
Signal FM. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

