<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Health, Social Welfare Minister Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1903002394 Caracas EL GLOBO in Spanish 18 Mar 94 p 46 </F>
<F P=103> PA1903002394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas EL GLOBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Liz Martinez] </F>
  [Text] Health and Social Welfare Minister Vicente Perez 
Davila presented his irrevocable resignation yesterday. Health 
problems related to his gastrointestinal system have forced the 
minister to resign. 
  Perez Davila coordinated the health area of President Rafael 
Caldera's government and later headed the liaison commission 
with the Health and Social Welfare Ministry. 
  In spite of his youth and having a good professional record, 
today Perez Davila is leaving the ministry for health reasons. 
He expressed his regrets to President Rafael Caldera. It was 
learned yesterday morning that Perez Davila sent a letter to the 
president of the Republic in which he explained the reasons for 
his resignation. In that letter he told President Rafael Caldera 
that he is sure the work of the new authorities at the Health 
and Social Welfare Ministry will be successful, because the 
persons working in the ministry are highly qualified and 
motivated. 
  President Caldera will now have to appoint a new health and 
social welfare minister, which must be a person highly qualified 
to direct a ministry confronting a serious hospital crisis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

