<F P=103> PA1903034194 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas EL GLOBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Maturin -- Education authorities in Monagas State 
decided on Thursday to suspend classes until further notice 
"given the students' continuous protests in the city. The 
protests were provoked by an increase in public transportation 
fares. [no closing quotation mark as published] 
  Monagas State Education Director Lidee de Ascanio made the 
announcement, saying that "the suspension of education 
activities applies to the kindergarten, elementary, and junior 
and senior high school levels in all public schools in the 
state." 
  Ascanio also urged representatives and members of the 
education community to honor the decision until the state's 
public transportation situation returns to normal. 
  A tense atmosphere prevailed in the city yesterday following 
the recent protests. 

