<H3> <TI>   Supreme Court Appoints Military Court Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1903152394 Caracas EL DIARIO DE CARACAS in Spanish 18 Mar 
94 p 10 </F>

<F P=103> PA1903152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas EL DIARIO DE CARACAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to unofficial reports, the Supreme Court 
of Justice, during a plenary session, has appointed the members 
of the Military Court for the 1994-99 term. 
  Army General Juan Manuel Bogado Velasquez was appointed 
Military Court president, replacing Gen. Ubaldo Jose Lopez 
Barrios. 
  The magistrates have appointed as nonvoting members Navy 
Captain Francisco Hedia Robledo and Army Colonel Ramon Moreno 
Natera, an investigator in the 4 February events. The third 
nonvoting member will be an Air Force officer yet to be 
appointed. 
  The court liaison will be selected from among these three 
officers, and the court reporter will still be Navy Captain 
Freddy Jose Ribas Pacheco, an investigator of the 27 November 
events and of some of the most important cases in military 
justice. Navy Captain Francisco Ortega Jugo will be assistant 
reporter. Ortega is currently a Defense Ministry legal adviser 
and was a Permanent War Council magistrate in Caracas. 

</TEXT>

