<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Caldera Continues To Pardon Military Coupists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2003154794 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2003154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Just as expected, President Rafael Caldera, who has 
maintained his pacification policy, has pardoned additional 
military groups linked to the 27 February [1992] coup attempt. 
At 1330, Lieutenant Colonel Jesus Urdaneta Hernandez, Major 
Pedro Emilio Alastre Lopez, Captain Wilmer Barrientos Fernandez, 
Capt. Miguel Rodriguez Torres, Capt. Luis Henry Jatar, Lt. Oscar 
Carrizal Flores, Lt. Florencio Porras Equezuria, and Lt. Nicolas 
Tejas Arrieta were freed. The usual gestures of happiness could 
be seen among friends and relatives awaiting them at the doors 
of the San Carlos headquarters from where they were transferred 
to their respective posts. 
  Only two were discharged: Lt. Urdenta Hernandez and Maj. 
Alastre Lopez. Reporters waited in vain for two hours for the 
announced statements by Lt. Col. Urdaneta, who decided to 
quickly leave the area instead. Only 29 cases remain, and they 
expect to be pardoned in the coming weeks. 

</TEXT>

