<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuban Minister Vecino Alegret Lectures at War College </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1803231294 Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 
18 Mar 94 p A4 </F>

<F P=103> PY1803231294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rio de Janeiro -- For the first time in 45 years the 
War College (ESG) opened its doors to a hero of the Cuban 
revolution. About 60 professors, and officers and civilians were 
in the college auditorium to listen to a lecture by Cuban Higher 
Education Minister Fernando Vecino Alegret, who fought next to 
Fidel Castro and was vice minister of the Cuban Revolutionary 
Armed Forces. "Times change," said the former officer, who faced 
in a natural way the fact that the school was a center for 
anti-communist preaching during the military regime. ESG 
Commander Brigadier Sergio Ferolla said: "The doors of the 
school are open to all without restrictions." 

</TEXT>

