<H3> <TI>   PRD Members, Police Clash in Guerrero State </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1803164394 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1803164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] There was a confrontation in Guerrero State between 
Party of the Democratic Revolution [PRD] members and state 
public security agents in Cutzamala de Pinzon, in the area of 
Tierra Caliente. The confrontation occurred when PRD members 
staged a demonstration to demand the dismissal of Mayor (Ramperi 
Suarez Berrun). 
  Policemen prevented the PRD members from seizing the 
municipal building, triggering the confrontation and some 
shooting. State authorities said at first two policemen died in 
the confrontation while another six were injured. The PRD state 
leadership revealed while two members received bullet wounds and 
many others suffered bruises, no one died. 
  In the meantime, Cutzamala de Pinzon is living in a climate 
of tension. 

</TEXT>

