Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Salvador, 20 Mar (ACAN) -- Ruben Zamora, 
presidential candidate of the Salvadoran left, has said there 
will be runoff presidential elections, and he rejected the 
ruling ARENA [Nationalist Republican Alliance] party has won the 
elections. 
  Zamora has added there were serious irregularities, as 
former 
guerrilla commanders reported earlier, that prevented thousands 
of people from casting their votes. He has vowed these 
irregularities will not happen again in the runoff elections, 
which he expects to win with the support of other opposition 
forces. 

